TODO:Neither dead nor alive, cursed and hiding from prying eyes, the Veiled has learned the same powers that caused his condition. He’s full of hate towards the undead, yet after ages of suffering he is in control of the same strange necromancy. It is not intended for reviving the dead, but for salvaging those not yet departed. His strength grows as he nears death, as the closer he gets to freeing himself from his damnation, the harder it is to keep this energy under control.

TODO:The only purpose of his veil is to hide his unholy body from anyone’s sight. The staff merely helps the Veiled to control his curse, and force it to submit to his will. His swordbreaker might seem to be for self-defense, yet its purpose is to weaken his foes even further.

TODO:Unable to feel the warmth of fire, taste food, or see dreams, the Veiled eschews others’ company and gets absorbed in his ancient, imperishable memories. Solitude either brings him peace, or strengthens his regrets. But if necessary, he will give his life force to anyone who might need it more than him.
